This paper discusses the concept of collaborating robots, which falls under the field of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also mentions the use of swarm intelligence and self-organization, which are topics related to multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the potential for coordinated sensing and interaction with the environment, which falls under the field of control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper mentions the use of nature-inspired meta-heuristics such as Ant colony optimization and Particle swarm Optimization, which are topics related to neural networks and evolutionary computation (cs.NE).
